lead_paragraph: The Jackson State men's tennis team has been placed on probation and its former coach has received a two-year show-cause penalty after the NCAA ruled he allowed an ineligible player to compete under an eligible player's name.

headline.print_headline: Former Jackson State Tennis Coach Gets Show-Cause Penalty
